what is node?

node is a javascript run time environment built over chrome v8  engine and c++ for executing javascript code.
 it can be used for buliding highly scalable , data intensive and real time apps

node architecture?

node works on asynchronous architechture / non blocking architecture , ie a thread is assigned to a particular work and when the work is being executed ,and the thread is free, it gets assigned to another work , thus utilising server and memory efficiently and reducing cost of operation.


